{
  "name": "Forge Factory Lab — Sr. Atlas Health Monitor",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛰️ Sr. Atlas — Forge Factory Lab\n### Health Monitor & Supervisor (Phase 2)\n\n**Philosophy:** Knowledge, validation and truth come before automation.\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Trigger (Manual or Schedule)\n2. Poll the 3 core services in parallel\n3. Merge the responses\n4. Build the structured **Sr. Atlas** report\n5. Decide: OPERATIONAL vs ALERT / DEGRADED\n\nSr. Atlas is the intelligent orchestrator. n8n executes the automations.",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "note-overview-0001",
      "name": "Sticky — Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-260, 60]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### 🔐 Future AI — API Key Handling\n\n**Never hardcode the key.**\n\nThis disabled HTTP node already reads the key from an environment variable:\n\n`Authorization: Bearer {{$env.SR_ATLAS_AI_API_KEY}}`\n\n**Where to set it (Windows Server 2022):**\n1. Stop n8n.\n2. In the n8n startup environment (PowerShell / .env / service), add:\n   `SR_ATLAS_AI_API_KEY=your_real_key_here`\n3. Restart n8n.\n\n**Preferred alternative — n8n Credentials:**\nCredentials → New → *Header Auth* (or provider credential) → paste key there, then switch this node's `Authentication` to that credential. Keys stored in Credentials are encrypted at rest.\n\nEnable this node only when the AI endpoint is ready.",
        "height": 420,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "note-aikey-0002",
      "name": "Sticky — AI Key Safety",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
